<section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-container">
        <details>
            <summary>Does granite stain?</summary>
            <p>Granite is porous and can stain if spills are not cleaned up promptly. Sealing the surface helps to prevent staining.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>Does quartz scratch?</summary>
            <p>Quartz is very scratch-resistant, but not scratch-proof. It can be scratched by sharp objects under high pressure.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>Can I put hot pans on quartz?</summary>
            <p>It is not recommended. The resin in quartz countertops can be damaged by extreme heat, leading to discoloration or cracking.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>Which is more affordable in Kansas City?</summary>
            <p>Costs for both granite and quartz can vary. Generally, some entry-level granite can be more affordable, but high-end granite is more expensive than most quartz.</p>
        </details>
    </div>
</section>
